                        12. CHECKSUM

                - A CONCISE-RFC document MUST follow a specific
                "metadata item structure".

                    - Metadata Item Structure:

                        - RFC: CONCISE-RFC-<XXXXXX>
                        - GROUP: <GROUP PROJECT NAME>
                        - TITLE: <UNIQUE AND CONCISE DOCUMENT TITLE>
                        - ACRONYM: <UACDT>
                        - AUTHOR: <FIRST NAME> <LAST NAME>
                        - CONTACT: <email>
                        - CATEGORY: (SPECIFICATION|INFORMATIONAL|EXPERIMENTAL)
                        - STATUS: (DRAFT|REVIEW|STABLE|DEPRECATED|OBSOLETE)
                        - VERSION: <XXXXXX>-<X.X.X>
                        - CREATED: <YYYY-MM-DD>
                        - MODIFIED: <YYYY-MM-DD>
                        - CHECKSUM: <SHA-256>

                - Each "metadata item content" of CONCISE-RFC document MUST follow
                a specific structure.

                    - Metadata Item Content:

                        - RFC:

                            - The RFC item MUST contain the version name of the
                            CONCISE-RFC format used by this document.

                        - GROUP:

                            - The GROUP item MUST contain the name of the project
                            category.

                        - TITLE:

                            - The TITLE item MUST have a maximum of 5 letter word.

                        - ACRONYM:

                            - The ACRONYM item MUST have 5 uppercase alphanumeric
                            characters.

                        - AUTHOR:

                            - The AUTHOR item MUST NOT be modified unless original
                            author transfers ownership.

                        - CONTACT:

                            - The CONTACT item MUST contain the email address of
                            the author.

                        - CATEGORY:

                            - Specification means this document is standard.
                            - Informational means this is a supporting document.
                            - Experimental means this document is a prototype.

                        - STATUS:

                            - Draft means this document in a work in progress.
                            - Review means this document is being audited.
                            - Stable means this document is in production.
                            - Deprecated means this document will soon be obsolete.
                            - Obsolete means this document was deprecated and
                            unsupported.

                        - VERSION:

                            - The VERSION item MUST be the version of this
                            document.
                            - The VERSION item MUST be composed of 6 digits
                            followed by the SEMVER format.

                        - CREATED:

                            - The CREATED item MUST contain the date this document
                            was created.

                        - MODIFIED:

                            - The MODIFIED item MUST contain date this document was
                            modified.

                        - CHECKSUM:

                            - The CHECKSUM item MUST contain the SHA-256 hash value
                            of this document as per result of running the
                            scripts/validate-concise-document.ps1 script.

